<i>I came, I saw, I nuked the crap out of everything in sight!</i><p>
<span style="font-size: 14px; font-famliy: arial"><b>Moordian Killbringer<br>Warrior of 22 Battle Scars</b><br><i>Dwarven LaMachine of Death</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushikariiapoccalypse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 211<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/01 5:23:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fletching</span><hr size=1> if he's going to be a mule make an erudite wizzie or something, it's always nice to have mules that can move around under his own power i guess. getting him to 20 shouldn't be too hard as well.<br>
<br>
my warrior has 100 int with a batskull earring, stein of mogguk, and a throneblade yak. his fletching is at 192 now, and, i am not sure whether i want to go any farther with it due to costs of supplies.but i like to have my warrior with the skill to pass time during hunts and waiting on groups.<br>
<br>
also over on <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com">www.eqtraders.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> there is a really nice excel spreadsheet on the cheapest routes to advance skills as well.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugaldilororetur.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galdilor Oretur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/01 9:03:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Making money with Fletching</span><hr size=1> Shikarii, you are so close to making money with fletching.  With a decent charisma and skill around 195 or so, you can reliably start making money by making arrows and selling them back to the vendor.  Once you get to 200, then a positive cashflow is almost guaranteed.  I have made 50pp in fifteen to twenty minutes of fletching.  Okay, I won't get rich, but if you are just passing time, it is a nice benefit.<br>
<br>
If you are not looking for a high level tradeskill mule, then a High Elf Enchanter is a nice option as the tradeoff between INT and CHA is very good.  Keeps your purchasing costs low and resale values higher.  Just make sure they are agnostic to reduce conflicts with others. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushikariiapoccalypse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/4/01 10:07:33 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Making money with Fletching</span><hr size=1> in steps my little mule, my Bard Kushtaka.<br>
<br>
i beefed him up to around 148 charisma, and, his charismatic carillion song helps the prices along rather nicely, especially when buying 100 or so steel arrow shafts. <br>
<br>
he usually does the majority of my buying and selling, rarely do i keep the good arrows i make and i usually only take a 15 - 25% loss on the arrows now .  <br>
<br>
